questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;A&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part A&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(20, 20, 20); background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);&quot;&gt;possessive adjective&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;her&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part A&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the sentence is wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Her&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a possessive adjective.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;possessive adjective&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;sits before a noun (or a pronoun) to show who or what owns it.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It modifies a noun.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Marie&amp;nbsp;brushed them away and returned to &lt;strong&gt;her&lt;/strong&gt; prayer.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Hers&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a possessive pronoun.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Possessive pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;show that something belongs to someone.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Some&amp;nbsp;possessive pronouns are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;my, mine, our, ours, its, his, her, hers, their, theirs, your, and yours.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hers&lt;/strong&gt; is a tragic story. &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this sentence, the subject&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;friend&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;belongs to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;hers&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;possessive adjective&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;her&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;should be replaced by the&amp;nbsp;possessive&amp;nbsp;pronoun&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;hers&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to make it grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;A&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;A friend of &lt;strong&gt;hers&lt;/strong&gt;, who is a florist, asks if she can advertise on the site.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​​​&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Possessive pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;include&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;my, mine, our, ours, its, his, her, hers, their, theirs, your and yours.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These are all words that demonstrate ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the book belongs to me, then it is mine.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the book belongs to her, then it is hers.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;What&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;mine&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yours&lt;/span&gt;, my friend.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2&lt;/b&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;Consolidate&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;fractate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to break or cause to break into pieces; it relates to dividing or fragmenting something. (टूटना या टुकड़ों में विभाजित होना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The vase fell from the table and fractated into several pieces.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Consolidate&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means to make something stronger or more solid; it refers to combining elements into a unified whole, which is the opposite of breaking or fractating. (मजबूत बनाना या एकीकृत करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The company decided to consolidate its operations to improve efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the antonym of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;fractate&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;consolidate&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2&lt;/strong&gt; i.e. &lt;b&gt;Consolidate&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Rupture&lt;/strong&gt; (फटना): The act of breaking or bursting suddenly.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The pipe ruptured due to excessive pressure.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fragment&lt;/strong&gt; (खंड): A small piece or part broken off something.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The archaeologist discovered a fragment of ancient pottery.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Infringe&lt;/strong&gt; (उल्लंघन करना): To actively break the terms of a law or agreement.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Copying someone&amp;#39;s work without permission infringes copyright laws.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Good news&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given Idiom&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Music to one&amp;#39;s ears&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;means Something that is pleasing to hear, such as good news (कुछ ऐसा जो सुनने में अच्छा लगे, जैसे कि अच्छी खबर)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example - When Michelle heard that her son and daughter-in-law were going to have a baby, it was music to her ears.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, the meaning of the idiom &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;music to one&amp;#39;s ears&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;good news&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Hence, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option (4).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;B&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part B&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the sentence.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The use of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(20, 20, 20); background-color: rgb(254, 254, 254);&quot;&gt;possessive adjective&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;their&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Part B&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the sentence is wrong.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Their&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a possessive adjective.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;possessive adjective&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;sits before a noun (or a pronoun) to show who or what owns it.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It modifies a noun.
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;It is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;their&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;dog.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Theirs&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is a possessive pronoun.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Possessive pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;show that something belongs to someone.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Some&amp;nbsp;possessive pronouns are&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;my, mine, our, ours, its, his, her, hers, their, theirs, your and yours.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The bag is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;theirs&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;In this sentence, the subject&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;money&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;belongs to&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;theirs&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Therefore, the&amp;nbsp;possessive adjective&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;their&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;should be replaced by the&amp;nbsp;possessive&amp;nbsp;pronoun&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;theirs&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to make it grammatically correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;B&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;The rest of the money was&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;theirs&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to spend as they pleased.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;​​​&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Possessive pronouns&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;include&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;my, mine, our, ours, its, his, her, hers, their, theirs, your and yours.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;These are all words that demonstrate ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the book belongs to me, then it is mine.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;If the book belongs to her, then it is hers.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;What&amp;#39;s&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;mine&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;yours&lt;/span&gt;, my friend.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Option 2 (Practicality)&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Nephelococcygia&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the act of imagining or finding shapes in clouds, typically an imaginative or fanciful activity. (बादलों में आकृतियाँ देखने की कल्पना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;As children, we spent hours in nephelococcygia, spotting animals and castles in the clouds.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Practicality&amp;quot; &lt;/strong&gt;is the quality of being practical, realistic, or concerned with actual use rather than imaginative or fanciful ideas. (व्यावहारिकता)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The practicality of the new design was appreciated by all the engineers.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the opposite of &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Nephelococcygia&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Practicality&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;, as it represents a grounded, realistic approach rather than an imaginative or fanciful one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Option 2 (Practicality)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;ध्यान केंद्रित करना&lt;/span&gt;): The center of interest or activity, or the ability to concentrate on a task.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;She maintained her focus despite the noisy environment.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Alertness &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;चेतना&lt;/span&gt;): The state of being attentive or watchful.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The security guard&amp;#39;s alertness prevented a possible theft.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Awareness &lt;/strong&gt;(&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(33, 37, 41);&quot;&gt;जागरूकता&lt;/span&gt;): The state or ability to perceive, feel, or be conscious of events, objects, or sensory patterns.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;Public awareness about health issues has increased significantly.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;3&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt; i.e. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;and the gilded altarpieces that had&amp;nbsp;tarnished&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The sentence is about the restoration of a Baroque cathedral, focusing on preserving intricate stucco work and gilded altarpieces.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The verb &amp;quot;tarnished&amp;quot; is incorrect in this context because it suggests an action completed in the past, whereas the context requires the passive voice to indicate that the altarpieces were affected by external factors over time.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The correct word should be &amp;quot;had been tarnished,&amp;quot; which is the appropriate past perfect passive form to show that the tarnishing occurred due to decades of exposure to industrial pollutants and humidity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Correct sentence:&lt;/span&gt; The restoration of the Baroque cathedral was not so much an attempt to modernize the structure as it was a dedicated effort to preserve the intricate stucco work and the gilded altarpieces that had &lt;strong&gt;been tarnished&lt;/strong&gt; by decades of exposure to industrial pollutants and humidity.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Passive Voice Usage:&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure:&lt;/strong&gt; Subject + had been + past participle.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; The documents had been destroyed before the meeting.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Usage:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to describe an action that was performed on the subject in the past.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Past Perfect Tense:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Structure:&lt;/strong&gt; Subject + had + past participle.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt; She had finished her homework before dinner.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Usage:&lt;/strong&gt; Used to describe an action completed before another action in the past.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;surpasses&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate synonym of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;exceeds&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;surpasses&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exceeds&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to be more than a particular number or amount. (संख्&amp;zwj;या या मात्रा विशेष से अधिक हो जाना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The weight of the bag should not &lt;strong&gt;exceed&lt;/strong&gt; 20 kilos.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Surpasses&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to do something better than somebody/something else or better than expected. (दूसरों से बेहतर या आशा से बढ़कर काम करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;The success of the film &lt;strong&gt;surpassed&lt;/strong&gt; all expectations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;i&gt;surpasses.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the &lt;strong&gt;meaning &lt;/strong&gt;of other words:

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;reduces&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to make something less or smaller in quantity, price, size, etc. (मात्रा, क़ीमत, आकार आदि की दृष्टि से घटाना; छोटा करना)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;diminishes&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to become or to make something smaller or less important; decreases. (छोटा होना या छोटा करना, महत्व घटाना; कम होना या करना)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;multiplies&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;to increase a number by the number of times mentioned. (किसी अंक को निर्दिष्ट संख्&amp;zwj;या से गुणा करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;damage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Revive&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means to return to consciousness or life;&amp;nbsp;become active or flourishing again.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;She tried to &lt;strong&gt;revive &lt;/strong&gt;the unconscious woman.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Marked option&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Damage&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;any change in a thing, often a physical object, that degrades it away from its initial state.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example -&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Earthquakes can cause terrible &lt;strong&gt;damage&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is clear that&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Revive&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Damage&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are opposite in meaning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 3.​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Freshen&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means to make something cleaner or brighter.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Continue&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means to keep happening or existing without stopping.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Restore&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means to bring back to a former, original, or normal condition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is: &lt;b&gt;Thundering&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Brontide&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; refers to a low rumbling sound, often associated with thunder or an earthquake. (गर्जन की ध्वनि)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The brontide echoed across the valley, signaling an approaching storm.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;Thundering&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; means producing a loud, deep sound similar to that of thunder. (गरजना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The thundering noise of the waterfall could be heard from miles away.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Both &amp;quot;brontide&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;thundering&amp;quot; are associated with loud, deep, and resonant sounds, making them synonymous.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is: &lt;strong&gt;Thundering&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here are the other options explained along with their Hindi meanings and example sentences:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ancient&lt;/strong&gt; (प्राचीन): Belonging to the very distant past and no longer in existence.

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The ancient ruins of the city still attract tourists from around the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Heavy-footed&lt;/strong&gt; (भारी कदमों वाला): Moving with heavy or clumsy steps.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The heavy-footed giant stomped through the forest, shaking the ground beneath him.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bronze-colored&lt;/strong&gt; (कांस्य रंग का): Having the color or appearance of bronze, a metallic brownish shade.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example: &lt;/strong&gt;The sunset painted the sky in a beautiful bronze-colored hue.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Here, the erroneous part is&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;at the movie hall&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The error lies in the part&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;at the movie hall&amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;of the sentence.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;At&amp;rdquo; i&lt;/strong&gt;s used when you are at the top, bottom or end of something; at a specific address; at a general location; and at a point.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;I will meet you &lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;at&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; the school.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;ldquo;In&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt; is used in a space, small vehicle, water, neighborhood, city and country.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;My friend lives &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; Greektown.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;​As we are talking about being inside the movie hall, the word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;quot;at&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;must be substituted by &lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;in&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to make the sentence contextually correct.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;Option 4.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
	&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;​​&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct sentence&lt;/u&gt;:&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;Remember to switch off your mobile phone &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;in&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; the m&lt;/em&gt;o&lt;em&gt;vie hall.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;correct answer&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;option 3 &lt;/strong&gt;i.e. &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Emanicipation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;incorrect spelling &lt;/strong&gt;is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Emanicipation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;correct spelling &lt;/strong&gt;is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Emancipation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Emancipation&lt;/strong&gt;: (मुक्ति) the act of freeing someone from legal, social, or political restrictions.&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example&lt;/strong&gt;: &amp;quot;The emancipation of women was a major social change.&amp;quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the &lt;strong&gt;correct answer &lt;/strong&gt;is - &lt;strong&gt;Emanicipation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Embarrassment&lt;/strong&gt;- a feeling of self-consciousness, shame, or awkwardness.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exasperation&lt;/strong&gt;- a feeling of intense irritation or annoyance&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fermentation&lt;/strong&gt;- the chemical breakdown of a substance by bacteria, yeasts, or other microorganisms, typically involving effervescence and the giving off of heat.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is- &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to take the blame for something&lt;/span&gt;.&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given idiom is:&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Take the spear&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;accepting the full brunt of the punishment for something&lt;/em&gt;. (किसी चीज की सजा का पूरा खामियाजा भुगतना।)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The CEO &lt;strong&gt;took the spear &lt;/strong&gt;for his company&amp;#39;s less revenue.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;By&amp;nbsp;the above meaning and example, we can say that &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;to take the blame for something&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; is the correct answer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
Hence&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;is the appropriate answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s learn a synonym of the&amp;nbsp;given idiom:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To take the spear in one&amp;#39;s chest&lt;/strong&gt; -&amp;nbsp;to accept full blame for something (किसी बात का पूरा दोष स्वीकार करना)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Tina declared that though Preeti might do her worst, she could not harm her.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The given sentence is a&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct speech,&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and we need to convert it into an&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;direct&amp;nbsp;speech.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;We follow these rules in Direct-Indirect speech&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The reporting verb&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;#39;said&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;changes to &amp;quot;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;declared&lt;/span&gt;&amp;quot; in the indirect speech because the direct speech is given as a statement.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;Let&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; changes to &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;might&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot; in indirect speech.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The verb &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;cannot&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; changes to the&amp;nbsp;pronoun &amp;#39;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;could not&lt;/span&gt;&amp;#39; in indirect speech.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;inverted commas (&amp;quot;...&amp;quot;)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;are replaced with the&amp;nbsp;conjunction&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;that&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;to show the indirect speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;comma (,)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is omitted&amp;nbsp;to show the indirect speech part.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;first word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the indirect speech is in&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;capital letters.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;option 1.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;The indirect sentence is:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;Tina declared that though Preeti might do her worst, she could not harm her.&lt;/p&gt;

