&lt;div&gt;Let us know the meaning of other word&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Estimation&lt;/strong&gt;: judgement, calculated guess&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reviews:&lt;/strong&gt; general survey, formal inspection&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Judgement:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt; an opinion or estimate so formed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;em&gt;The correct&amp;nbsp;answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Assessment&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Individual&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Refer to the passage &amp;quot;&amp;nbsp;A conceptual flaw pointed out by experts is that it goes against the separation of powers. It allows ___5___&amp;nbsp;legislators to encroach on the planning and implementation duties of the administration&amp;quot;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;Individual&amp;#39; is the word which fits in the sentence grammatically as we need an adjective to qualify the noun &amp;#39;legislators&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Individual (adj)&lt;/strong&gt; means &lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Relating to a single person or thing as opposed to more than one&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;. Rest of the options are nouns and so they can be easily eliminated&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, Option 3&amp;nbsp; is the correct answer&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Human&lt;/strong&gt;: having human form or attribute&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Group&lt;/strong&gt;: two or more figures forming a complete unit&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Individual&lt;/strong&gt;: single quantity of a thing or single person&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Individual&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Directions&lt;/strong&gt;: &lt;strong&gt;This question consists of six sentences of a passage. The first and sixth sentences are given as S1 and S6. The middle four sentences in each have been jumbled up and labelled as P, Q, R and S. You are required to find the proper sequence of the four sentences and mark your response accordingly.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S1: Drugmaker Hetero on Monday said that it has received a prequalification approval from World Health Organization (WHO) for its generic version of Pfizer&amp;rsquo;s Covid-19 oral antiviral treatment candidate nirmatrelvir.&lt;br /&gt;
P: Hetero&amp;rsquo;s combi-pack Nirmacom will contain nirmatrelvir 150 mg (2 tablets) and ritonavir 100mg (1 tablet).&lt;br /&gt;
Q: WHO made a strong recommendation for nirmatrelvir and ritonavir for mild and moderate Covid-19 patients at highest risk of hospital admission, such as unvaccinated, aged, or immunosuppressed patients.&lt;br /&gt;
R: &amp;ldquo;This is the first prequalification for a generic version of Pfizer&amp;rsquo;s Covid-19 oral antiviral drug &amp;lsquo;Paxlovid&amp;rsquo;, which the WHO called the best therapeutic choice for high-risk patients to date,&amp;rdquo; a note from Hetero said.&lt;br /&gt;
S: The cost to a patient for the entire course would be about ₹4900, an industry-source said, adding that it is currently sold to hospitals and government institutions only. It&amp;rsquo;s likely to be about $70, cost to patient for the course, in low and middle income countries, the sourced added.&lt;br /&gt;
S6: The product will be available by prescription and should be initiated as soon as possible after diagnosis of Covid-19 and within five days of symptom onset.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;RPSQ&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt; introduces the main topic of the passage, which is the prequalification approval from the World Health Organization (WHO) for Hetero&amp;#39;s generic version of Pfizer&amp;#39;s Covid-19 oral antiviral treatment candidate nirmatrelvir.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;R&lt;/strong&gt; explains that this is the first prequalification for a generic version of Pfizer&amp;#39;s Covid-19 oral antiviral drug &amp;quot;Paxlovid&amp;quot;, which the WHO has called the best therapeutic choice for high-risk patients to date.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt; describes the composition of Hetero&amp;#39;s combi-pack Nirmacom, which will contain nirmatrelvir 150 mg (2 tablets) and ritonavir 100mg (1 tablet).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S&lt;/strong&gt; mentions that the product will be available by prescription and should be initiated as soon as possible after diagnosis of Covid-19 and within five days of symptom onset. It also notes that the cost to a patient for the entire course would be about ₹4900 in India and about $70 in low and middle income countries, and that it is currently sold to hospitals and government institutions only.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt; mentions the WHO&amp;#39;s strong recommendation for nirmatrelvir and ritonavir for mild and moderate Covid-19 patients at highest risk of hospital admission, such as unvaccinated, aged, or immunosuppressed patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S6&lt;/strong&gt; concludes the passage by noting that the product will be available by prescription and should be initiated as soon as possible after diagnosis of Covid-19 and within five days of symptom onset.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;RPSQ&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt; is the correct answer.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct paragraph&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;S1&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Drugmaker Hetero on Monday said that it has received a prequalification approval from World Health Organization (WHO) for its generic version of Pfizer&amp;rsquo;s Covid-19 oral antiviral treatment candidate nirmatrelvir.&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;R&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;This is the first prequalification for a generic version of Pfizer&amp;rsquo;s Covid-19 oral antiviral drug &amp;lsquo;Paxlovid&amp;rsquo;, which the WHO called the best therapeutic choice for high-risk patients to date,&amp;rdquo; a note from Hetero said.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;P&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Hetero&amp;rsquo;s combi-pack Nirmacom will contain nirmatrelvir 150 mg (2 tablets) and ritonavir 100mg (1 tablet).&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;S&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;The cost to a patient for the entire course would be about ₹4900, an industry-source said, adding that it is currently sold to hospitals and government institutions only. It&amp;rsquo;s likely to be about $70, cost to patient for the course, in low and middle income countries, the sourced added.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Q&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;WHO made a strong recommendation for nirmatrelvir and ritonavir for mild and moderate Covid-19 patients at highest risk of hospital admission, such as unvaccinated, aged, or immunosuppressed patients.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;S6&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;The product will be available by prescription and should be initiated as soon as possible after diagnosis of Covid-19 and within five days of symptom onset.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Sentences of a paragraph are given below. While the first and the last sentences (S1 and S6) are in the correct order, the sentences in between are jumbled up and named P, Q, R, S. Arrange the sentences in the correct order to form a meaningful and coherent paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(S1) Newspapers, especially of the popular variety, aim to do two things: to inform and to entertain.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(P) Entertainment may be principally found in the centre pages of the newspaper in some of the feature articles and in some local news stories.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Q) The principal aim of the short news report on the front pages is to inform.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(R) Most newspapers are published daily, and the news reporters must make sure that they have up-to-the minute news.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(S) In their news reports they will aim to create a sense of immediacy, to convey the impression that they have &amp;lsquo;rushed&amp;rsquo; the news to the reader and &amp;lsquo;that the information contained is the very latest.&amp;rsquo;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(S6) Reporters also wish to create a sense of authenticity, that is, that their news is accurate and genuine.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
The correct answer is &amp;quot;&lt;strong&gt;P, Q, R, S&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;quot;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The paragraph is about the aims and content of newspapers, with a focus on informing and entertaining readers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The first sentence (S1) sets the context and purpose of the paragraph.
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The sentences (P) and (Q) explain how newspapers achieve their aims of informing and entertaining readers.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The sentence (R) provides additional information about the daily publication of newspapers and the need for up-to-date news.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The sentences (S) and (S6) highlight the importance of immediacy and authenticity in news reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Thus, it can be concluded that the correct chronology of the given sentences would be: PORS.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Hence, &lt;strong&gt;the correct answer is option 4.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

questions.statement:
&lt;p&gt;Choose the most logical order of sentences from among the four choices to construct a coherent paragraph.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A. The man who is perpetually hesitating over which of the two things he will do first, will do neither.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;B. He fluctuates from opinion to opinion and veers like a weather-cock.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;C. Instead of being progressive in anything, he will be at best stationary and most probably regress in all.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;D. It is only the man who first consults wisely, then resolves firmly, that can advance to eminence in any time.&lt;/p&gt;

questions.explanation:
&lt;div&gt;&lt;span&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A: &amp;quot;The man who is perpetually hesitating over which of the two things he will do first, will do neither.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This sentence introduces the central theme: the futility of indecision. It establishes the subject and sets the tone for the paragraph. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;B: &amp;quot;He fluctuates from opinion to opinion and veers like a weather-cock.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This sentence elaborates on the concept of hesitation introduced in A. It provides a vivid description of the indecisive person&amp;#39;s behavior, illustrating their lack of direction. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;C: &amp;quot;Instead of being progressive in anything, he will be at best stationary and most probably regress in all.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This sentence explains the consequences of the behavior described in A and B. It logically follows by outlining the negative outcomes of indecision, which are stagnation or decline. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;D: &amp;quot;It is only the man who first consults wisely, then resolves firmly, that can advance to eminence in any time.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This sentence provides a contrasting perspective and offers a solution. It presents the opposite scenario: a decisive person who achieves success. This makes it a suitable concluding sentence, offering a resolution to the problem of indecision discussed earlier. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option&amp;nbsp;3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Correct Paragraph:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;&amp;quot;The man who is perpetually hesitating over which of the two things he will do first, will do neither. He fluctuates from opinion to opinion and veers like a weather-cock. Instead of being progressive in anything, he will be at best stationary and most probably regress in all. It is only the man who first consults wisely, then resolves firmly, that can advance to eminence in any time.&amp;quot;&lt;/em&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt; &lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;1: A, B, D, C&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This order places the contrasting example (D) before the explanation of the consequences (C), which disrupts the logical flow. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2: B, A, C, D&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This order starts with a description of behavior (B) before introducing the main idea (A), which is less effective. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;4: C, D, A, B&lt;/strong&gt; &amp;ndash; This order begins with the consequences (C), making it difficult to understand without first establishing the cause (A and B). &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
